    "recap_headline": "Bowling Green State University Athletics",
    "recap_text": "BOWLING GREEN, Ohio\n\u2013\nThe Bowling Green State University baseball team continued the weekend series against Ohio on Saturday (March 21) at Steller Field, but not before a celebration of the new renovations to the facility. Prior to the game, BGSU held an on-field recognition and ribbon cutting for the new turf, lights and other new aspects at\u00a0Steller Field. As for the game, Ohio jumped out to a 6-0 lead, but the Falcons fought back. A three-run home run from\nPauly Mancino\nin the seventh inning cut the score to 8-5, but the home run marked the final runs of the day to force a rubber match between the Falcons and Bobcats on Sunday (March 22) at 12 p.m.\nHOW IT HAPPENED\nOhio scored the first runs of the game with four in the second inning. OU added two runs in the fourth to make it 6-0.\nAnthony Mitta\nled off the inning with a double to left center before moving to third on a grounder.\nAndrew DiLodovico\nlegged out a single to score Mitta for a 6-1 score through the fourth.\nVinny Salvione\nsingled to left with an error advancing him to third. Mitta put a ball in play to score Salvione, cutting the lead to 6-2.\nThe Bobcats answered with a two-run home run to make the score 8-2 at the seventh inning stretch.\nDiLodovico started the inning with a single up the middle. A single from\nZack Horky\nput two on, setting up a three run home run from\nPauly Mancino\nto close the gap to 8-5.\nSTAT LEADERS\nPauly Mancino\n: 1-for-3, 1 HR, 3 RBI, 1 R\nAnthony Mitta\n: 1-for-4, 1 2B, 1 RBI, 1 R\nZack Horky\n: 2-for-2, 1 R, 1 BB\nAndrew DiLovodico: 2-for-3, 1 RBI, 1 R, 1 BB\nVinny Salvione\n: 1-for-4, 1 R\nTy Roder\n: 2.1 IP, 1 H, 0 R/ER, 1 K\nFALCON STAT FACTS\nAndrew DiLodovico\nstayed hot at the plate for the Falcons with his second straight multi-hit game. DiLodovico now has a five-game hitting streak as well as a five-game scoring streak. During the five-game stretch, DiLodovico is 8-for-19 (.421) at the plate with six runs scored, four RBI, a triple and a home run.\nPauly Mancino\nbelted his second home run of the season with both coming in his last four games played. For Mancino, an Ohio transfer to BGSU, the three RBI from the round-trip marked a season-high for him.\nAnthony Mitta\ntallied his second double in as many days while scoring in both games of the series as well. Mitta has a hit in eight of the last nine games for the Falcons.\nZack Horky\nput together his third multi-hit game of the season, logging two hits. Horky has five hits in his last five games played.\nUP NEXT\nBowling Green and Ohio will conclude the weekend series on Sunday (March 22) with a newly adjusted start time of a 12 p.m. first pitch at Steller Field.\nAny schedule changes will be announced on BGSUFalcons.com as well as Twitter/X (@BGSU_Baseball).\nFollow the Falcons\nBe sure to follow the Falcons' baseball team on social media\nTwitter - @BGSU_Athletics and @BGSU_Baseball\nInstagram - 'bgfalcons' and 'bgsu_baseball'\nFacebook - 'BGSU Athletics'\nYouTube - 'Falcons Athletics'",
